Course.Title: ORGANIC CHEM LAB II
Course.Description:
This is the second half of a two-semester sequence in experimental organic chemistry. Students are expected to execute the fundamental laboratory techniques learned in CHEM 2581L to effectively accomplish single and multi-step syntheses. Synthetic reactions are chosen to reinforce the topics covered in lecture. Students are expected to utilize industry standard protocols, write professional lab notebooks/formal lab reports, characterize products using modern synthetic techniques such as NMR, IR, GC/MS. 

Prerequisite(s): CHEM 2581 and CHEM 2581L or Approved Petition Required.  

Co-requisite(s): CHEM 2582.

Course.Title: ORGANIC CHEMISTRY II
Course.Description: The second half of a two-semester sequence in organic chemistry for science majors. The remaining organic functional groups including aldehydes & ketones, carboxylic acids, acyl halides, anhydrides, esters, amides and amines are covered. More emphasis is placed on synthesis. The course may also include an introduction to the biochemistry of carbohydrates, lipids, protein and nucleic acids. Required for the Chemistry major.
